Detailed description of the collection
Registration and interaction with the Program
We will collect registration information (for example: first, last name, address, phone number and email address) when you register for EM Rewards+.
The types of information we collect depends on which product or service you use.
Sometimes you give information directly to us, our Sponsors, or our Service Providers, for example, when you register. We may also collect information in other interactions between us, such as when you:
fill out an online form or survey;
log into or update the settings or preferences on your account online;
register or enroll in our services;
enter a contest, sweepstakes or register for a marketing offer;
buy something at Participating Locations; or
contact our call center.
The EM Rewards+ App can collect information about your geolocation only when the App is installed and if you have given permission for location services. You can turn off location services in your phone or App settings, but this will mean that you lose some of the functionality of the App and as a result will need to scan the QR codes found on the pump.
ExxonMobil does not use or disclose any sensitive personal information (such as geolocation information) for purposes other than to perform the services you request (e.g. providing directions to nearest service station or paying at the pump via EMR+ App), or verify and maintain the quality or safety of our services or applications as permitted by applicable data privacy regulations.
In order to pay via third party Payment provider (such as Apple Pay or PayPal), you will be required to provide certain information to this authorised third party to support security, operations and servicing of the App and your payments. These third party payment providers operate independently of ExxonMobil. Make sure that you read the privacy policies of these payment providers, which is different from ExxonMobil’s Privacy Statement, so that you understand how they work, including what information they collect about you and how they use it.
In the EM Rewards+ App, you can enroll your phone number in the EM Rewards+ program and sign up to receive marketing messages via SMS. Your phone number will not be shared with Third Parties or used for non-ExxonMobil marketing/promotional purposes.
We (and our Service Providers or Third-Party Ad-Servers) also collect information through Cookies and App codes. Most Cookies will only collect De-Identified Information such as how you arrive at our website or your general location, but, certain Cookies may collect Personal Information. For example, clicking “Remember Me” at log-in would result in a cookie storing your username. You can decide if and how your computer will accept Cookies by configuring preferences or options in your web browser. However, if you choose to reject cookies, you may not be able to use certain online products, services or features of the website.
We may place Cookies when you visit our website or another company’s website where our ads appear or when you make purchases, request or personalize information, or register for certain services. If you accept the cookies used on our website or websites where our ads appear, you may give us access to information about your interests.
We (and our Service Providers or Third-Party Ad-Servers) may collect information using Cookies and App codes about:
the device you use to browse our websites or use our apps (for example, we may collect information about the operating system or the browser version and the type of device you use to open electronic communications from us);
DeviceID, crash logs, app interaction to maintain the quality and safety of our website and application.
the IP Address and information related to that IP Address (such as domain information, your internet provider and general geographic location);
browsing history on our websites or apps (such as what you search for, the pages you view, how long you stay, and how often you come back);
how you search for our websites or apps, from which website or app you came from, and which of our Sponsors’ websites you visit;
which ads or online content from us and our Sponsors you view, access, or click on;
whether you open our electronic communications and which parts you click on; and
the location of your mobile device or EM Rewards+ transactions.
We (and our Service Providers or Third-Party Ad-Servers) may also collect information made publicly available through third party platforms (such as online social media platforms), through online databases or directories, or that is otherwise legitimately obtained. The collection of this information is subject to the applicable third party’s terms of use and/or privacy statement.
2. Using Personal Information
We may use Online Information we collect about you on its own or combine it with Other Information to:
deliver products and services, including to:
recognize you when you return to our websites;
complete transactions;
tell you about updates to your accounts, products and services;
update you about new features, offers and benefits;
answer questions and respond to your requests made through our websites, call center, or apps and through third-party websites (including social media);
use the location of your mobile device for EM Rewards+ transactions;
determine how to best provide services to you and manage your accounts,
improve our websites or apps and make them easier to use;
advertise and market our products and services – and those of our Sponsors – including to:
present content that is tailored to your interests, including Targeted Advertising;
send or provide you with ads, promotions, and offers from us or our Sponsors;
analyze whether the ads, promotions, and offers are effective;
help us determine whether you may be interested in new products or services from us or our Sponsors;
conduct research and analysis, including to better understand our customers and our website or app users;
allow you to give feedback by rating and reviewing our products and services and those of our Sponsors;
produce data analytics, statistical research, and reports; and
review and change our products and services;
manage fraud and security risk, including to detect and prevent fraud or criminal activity;
safeguard the security of your information; and
use it in other ways as required or permitted by law or with your consent.
3. Terms of Financial Incentives
EM Rewards+ members can earn points for qualifying purchases upon presentation of an EM Rewards+ identifier, such as card, App, account number, or phone number associated with account, and may redeem those points at participating Exxon and Mobil service stations. The number of points earned for qualifying purchases and the value of points upon redemption are subject to change and may vary between goods and services according to temporary offers or promotions. Further, EM Rewards+ points are subject to expiration.
EM Rewards+ members may also be offered price discounts on certain goods or services. Where an incentive, discounted price, or service difference is provided to EM Rewards+ members for the collection or sharing of Personal Information, such incentive is directly related to the value of the Personal Information. Incentives may be subject to ExxonMobil receiving the purchasing member’s express direction to share information (which may include details of a discounted transaction or non-identifying Personal Information of the purchasing member) with Sponsors or retail suppliers associated with the discounted goods or services, when required by applicable law.
ExxonMobil does not treat consumers differently if they exercise a privacy right provided by governing law (such as those described below in Section 5.), however the processing of member Personal Information is required for administration of the program and provision of certain member discounts or benefits. Participation in EM Rewards+ is always voluntary and members may withdraw at any time.
The terms of the EM Rewards+ program, including details on earning points, using points, point expiration, and withdrawing from the program are more fully set forth in the EM Rewards+ Program Terms and Conditions available at
https://www.exxon.com/en/terms-conditions
.
Tobacco Rebates
One example of a financial incentive offered to EM Rewards+ members related to the collection of Personal Information is for certain tobacco purchases at participating stores. For example, purchase of certain tobacco products at participating stores may qualify the consumer for a discount. The consumer may be asked if they would like to provide an Exxon Mobil Rewards+ identifier (generally an EM Rewards+ account number or phone number) to receive a discounted price for the tobacco products. If the consumer opts-in, ExxonMobil will share details of the purchase along with a pseudonymized identifier (i.e., cannot be used to identify the specific consumer) with the tobacco supplier. In exchange, the participating retailer will receive a rebate equal to the discount in price received by the consumer.  ExxonMobil receives no monetary compensation for this collection and sharing of Personal Information. Participation in the program is entirely voluntary and consumers may refuse to provide the information at any time. Participating in a program does not preclude the consumer from exercising any applicable rights under California law.
4. Selling and Sharing of Personal Information
We will only share Personal Information as described below, and subject to your opt-in consent or right to opt-out where applicable:
with our Sponsors and Service Providers for online advertising or other marketing purposes (sharing of online Personal Information via Cookies is subject to opt-out, see Section 5 for more information) (if you do not want us to share your Personal Information, after you have enrolled please visit My Account page at www.EMrewards.com and “opt out” of sharing);
with regulatory authorities, courts, and governmental agencies to comply with legal orders, legal or regulatory requirements, and government requests;
with our Service Providers, Sponsors, regulatory authorities, and governmental agencies to detect and prevent fraud or criminal activity, and to protect the rights of EM Rewards+ or others;
with ExxonMobil Corporate Family;
with our Service Providers, including those who perform services for us and help us operate EM Rewards+ and our business (we require Service Providers to safeguard Personal Information and only use your Personal Information for the purposes we specify);
with credit card processing vendors or other third party payment providers in order to provide you payment functionality in our mobile application;
in the context of a sale of all or part of the ExxonMobil Corporate Family or their assets; or
for specific uses, products or services, or member financial incentives upon member opt-in consent.
You consent, acknowledge, and agree that we can transfer Personal Information to Service Providers or companies within the ExxonMobil Corporate Family throughout the world, for example, to process transactions and provide you with our products or services. Other countries may not have the same data protection laws as the country in which you initially provided the information. However, regardless of where we process your information, we will still protect it in the manner described in this Privacy Statement.
We prohibit our Sponsors from sharing information with other third parties / companies outside of EM Rewards+ or those unaffiliated with Exxon Mobil Corporation.
Aggregated Information or De-identified Information does not directly identify you individually; it helps us to analyze patterns among groups of people. We may share Aggregated Information or De-identified Information in several ways, for example:
for the same reasons as we might share Personal Information;
with Sponsors to help develop and market products or services and present targeted content, including Targeted Advertising;
with Sponsors to conduct analysis and research about customers, website and app users; or
with Third-Party Ad-Servers to place ads (including ads of our Sponsors) on various websites and apps, and to analyze the effectiveness of those ads;
ExxonMobil only discloses EM Rewards+ member Personal Information to fund or validate consumer discounts, and only with member opt-in consent provided at the time of Personal Information collection (for example, see details of the Tobacco Rebate program in the “Terms of Financial Incentives” section above).
In the past twelve months since this Privacy Statement took effect, for commercial purposes, we have processed or shared user preferences, information related to interaction of our sites for cross-context behavioral advertising via cookies of consumers to web and data analytics Service Providers, search engine and social media platform providers.
