5. Your rights
In accordance with applicable US laws, you may have the right to request:
Deletion
of your Personal Information (note that deletion of Personal Information processed with respect to administration of EM Rewards+ membership may require withdrawal of membership and potential loss of program benefits). If you request to delete your account or any personal information, which is required to create an account, such as Name, Email address, Loyalty membership ID, phone number, please note that we will cancel your account and delete your personal information. Additionally, if you request for us to delete your AARP member ID from your account or request to unlink your AARP membership from your account, please note that any additional benefits related to the partner programs will be lost.
Access
to specific pieces of information ExxonMobil has about you or more information about our data processing practices.
Correction
of any inaccurate personal data we maintain about you.
Opt-out from sale or sharing your data for cross-context behavioral advertising
Right to Opt-Out for the Purposes of Profiling:
you may have the right to opt-out of processing of personal data for purposes of profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects.
Appeals: To appeal our decision on your data subject requests, you may contact us at
data.privacy.office@exxonmobil.com
. Please enclose a copy of or otherwise specifically reference the decision you want to appeal. We will respond to your appeal in accordance with applicable law.
ExxonMobil will not discriminate against you for exercising your data subject rights, although some of the functionality and features available on the Service may change or no longer be available to you.  Any difference in the Services are related to the value provided.
In order to submit a verifiable consumer request to exercise your right to know about, delete, or correct your personal information, please visit ExxonMobil’s privacy program
landing page
where you may submit your request via email, web form.
US California consumers also can submit their privacy request via the 833-835-2644 toll free number. Please note, all the calls through the 833-835-2644 phone number will be recorded for quality assurance and data verification purposes.
When you submit a data privacy request, ExxonMobil will verify your identity by requesting you to provide your name, email address or other contact information, ExxonMobil account information (in case it is applicable), and the company brand with which you have a relationship.
Use of an authorized agent: You may be entitled, in accordance with applicable law, to submit a request through an authorized agent. To designate an authorized agent to exercise your rights and choices on your behalf, please provide your authorized agent with signed, written permission demonstrating that they have been authorized by you to act on your behalf. You may be required
Verify your own identity directly with us; or
Directly confirm with us that you provided the authorized agent permission to submit the request.
You also have a right to lodge a complaint to the data protection supervisory authority in your country.
For more information about the specific mechanisms available to exercise these rights, please submit a data privacy request on our
landing page
or contact the ExxonMobil Data Privacy Office at
data.privacy.office@exxonmobil.com
.
To facilitate our efforts to address your request, please let us know the circumstances in which you initially provided ExxonMobil with your personal data, e.g. in connection with a specific product or service.
Do-Not-Track Signals and Similar Mechanisms, such as Global Privacy Control on ExxonMobil US websites:  Some web browsers transmit "do-not-track" signals. We take action in response to these signals:  If the browser has Do Not Track enabled, cookies in this group will be disabled until explicit consent is received. We detect and honor your Global Privacy Control signal if the website browser add-in or extension is enabled at your end. Please see further information about the Global Privacy Control mechanism
here
.
To access the metrics and statistics about the fulfilment of the data subject rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act please click to
view the global English privacy policy here
.
6. How to Opt-out from Selling and Sharing of your Personal Information
ExxonMobil discloses EM Rewards+ member Personal Information only with member opt-in consent provided at the time of Personal Information collection.
ExxonMobil may share with third parties EM Rewards+ member Personal Information collected in the context of navigation of EM Rewards+ websites via Cookie for the purpose of cross-context behavioral advertising. You may opt-out of this sharing by following the cookie-banner instructions or by accessing the “Privacy center”/ “Privacy Center -  Do not sell or share my personal data” link at the bottom of our websites.
7. Keeping and Safeguarding Information
We have adopted security procedures to help protect against loss, misuse, and unauthorized access to the information you provide to us. Please note that no data transmission or storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. As a result, while we strive to protect your information and privacy, we cannot guarantee or warrant the security of any information you disclose or transmit. We take reasonable steps to securely destroy or permanently de-identify Personal Information when we no longer need it.
We will keep your Personal Information only as long as required to deliver our products and services, unless we are required by law or regulation or for litigation or regulatory reasons to keep it.
8. Defined Terms
Aggregated Information - data or information relating to multiple people which has been combined. Aggregated Information includes information that we create or compile from various sources, such as from transactions or certain data from Cookies.
ExxonMobil Corporate Family - any affiliate and subsidiary of, and any company owned or controlled by, Exxon Mobil Corporation.
Cookies - a cookie is a small data file that a website stores on your computer's hard drive. Similar technologies such as web beacons, pixels, gifs, and tags also do the same thing. We use the term Cookies in this Privacy Statement to refer to all technologies that collect information in this way.
De-identified Information - data or information, including pseudonymized data, that does not directly identify you to a third party. It includes information that we may collect from various sources, such as transactions or data from Cookies.
IP Address - a number assigned to a device when connecting to the Internet.
Online Information - data or information collected on the EM Rewards+ websites as well as on websites and apps of third parties relating to topics about our business which may include Personal Information, Aggregated Information and De-Identified Information.
Other Information - EM Rewards+ internal information (for example, transaction data), and other online and offline information we collect from or about you.
Participating Locations - participating Exxon and Mobil branded service stations operated by ExxonMobil branded wholesalers and locations of other Sponsors who may become a part of EM Rewards+.
Personal Information - Information that can identify a natural person, such as name, address, telephone number, and email address.
Service Providers - any vendor, and/or company that performs business operations on our behalf, such as in connection with EM Rewards+, information technology support, printing, mailing, and other communications services, marketing, data processing, servicing, collections, or ad management.
Sponsors - ExxonMobil branded wholesalers and retail companies, including site operators, with whom we conduct business. These Sponsors may become a part of EM Rewards+. These Sponsors may not have a direct contractual relationship with ExxonMobil.
Targeted Advertising - ads we or our Sponsors display on websites outside the ExxonMobil Corporate Family based on the preferences or interests inferred from data collected from a particular computer or device regarding web viewing behaviors over time and across different websites.
Third Party Ad-Servers - companies that provide the technology to place ads on websites (and apps) and track how ads perform. These companies may also place and access cookies on your device. The information they collect from our websites is in a form that does not identify you personally.
Exxon Mobil Rewards+™ Privacy Statement (2023)
